commitResults.messageTitle: Add DateTimeParser for Wanya to understand date and time
commitResults.messageBody:
DateTimeParser enable Wanya to recognise String of format
"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm" as dates and time respectively.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add exceptions and test for DateTimeParser
commitResults.messageBody:
Add checks to ensure program will not crash if date is not provided
or format of date is invalid. Remind users the correct format
required to add deadlines and events.

Conduct automated text-ui testing for regression testing.
Made some unecessary changes to master branch to be 1 commit ahead.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bug of missing details from Wanya file
commitResults.messageBody:
Reason: I should have changed the file name from Duke to Wanya
from the master branch before even creating the new branches, which
led to the changes made in the Level-8 branch to not be reflected in
the master Branch.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bug of date time format not displayed properly
commitResults.messageBody:
Initially, the date time format shown on the deadline and event
are in the DateTime format rather than my intended format. I have
missed out the function call when converting toString method.
Code is working as intended and conducted text-UI test.

Create 4 new classes
- Ui to deal with interaction with users
- Parser to make sense of the command user inputs
- TaskList to contain task list and handle tasks operations
- Storage to load and save task list

- Divide classes into packages
- Reformat tasks string format in Storage

commitResults.messageTitle: Edit Parser ability to check for empty task
commitResults.messageBody:
Tasks that have empty description such as "todo   "
is recognized as a valid task by the parser, even though
it should not be valid.
Trim function removes white spaces to fix the issue.

Add JUnit tests for DateTimeParser, Deadline, Event and Todo
Checks:
- parsing of date
- parsing of date with time
- parsing of incorrect date
- parsing of correct date with incorrect time

- deadline String representation
- deadline Storage String

- Event String representation
- Event Storage String

- ToDo String representation
- ToDo Storage String
Added JavaDoc comments to public methods and public classes

commitResults.messageTitle: Change method names for setter methods of boolean variables

commitResults.messageBody:
Users can now search for related tasks in task list with
a given keyword.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update find function to act differently if no match was found.
commitResults.messageBody:
Initially, when no match of keyword from current tasks in task list,
Wanya will still print "Here are the matching tasks:".

Wanya should not print that if there are no matching tasks.

Wanya now informs the user there are no matching tasks if there
are no matching tasks.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add GUI to replace text based interface
commitResults.messageBody:
Features implemented:
1. Add GUI (mainWindow, dialogBox and pictures)
2. Refactor functions method to return String instead of print

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Assertions to Parser and TaskList
commitResults.messageBody:
Include Assertions in current methods to verify underlying
assumptions in code to ensure mistakes made by the programmer
will not cause the entire bot to malfunction, especially when
loading saved files that may be corrupted.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code to improve code quality
commitResults.messageBody:
1. For methods that were previously too long, additional methods
were created to replace portions of the code within the if else
blocks to allow easier debugging in the future by isolating the method
that is causing the bug.

2. Avoid complicated expression in if statements. I calculated the
intermediate values separately and include the final value for the
condition in if statement.

3. Get rid of 'magic' string that are returned from functions. Add
a variable name to the String to self explain what does the String
represent before returning it.
